# LXC Image Builder Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and customize as needed
# The .env file should be added to .gitignore for security

# === BUILD CONFIGURATION ===
# Override default build parameters
#DIST=debian
#RELEASE=trixie
#ARCH=amd64
#VARIANT=cloud

# === SSH CONFIGURATION ===
# Create an SSH user for remote access
SSH_USER=admin

# Set password for SSH user (comment out to disable password auth)
SSH_PASSWORD=your_secure_password_here

# Path to SSH public key file (for key-based authentication)
# Uncomment and set the path to your public key
#SSH_KEY_FILE=/path/to/your/public/key.pub

# === SECURITY CONFIGURATION ===
# Set root password (comment out to leave root password unset)
ROOT_PASSWORD=your_root_password_here

# === ADVANCED CONFIGURATION ===
# Custom output directory
#OUTDIR=/custom/output/path

# Custom cache directory
#CACHE_DIR=/custom/cache/path

# Custom zip filename prefix
#ZIP_BASENAME=MyCustom_LXC_Image

# Container name during build (usually don't need to change)
#NAME=tmp-image

# === USAGE NOTES ===
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.template .env
# 2. Edit .env with your preferred settings
# 3. Add .env to .gitignore: echo ".env" >> .gitignore
# 4. Run the build: ./build-lxc-wrapper.sh
#
# Command line options will override these environment variables.
#
# For key-only authentication (no passwords):
# - Set SSH_USER and SSH_KEY_FILE
# - Comment out SSH_PASSWORD and ROOT_PASSWORD
# - This will disable password authentication in SSH config